Subject: ancestry category [HANCESTRO:0004]
Value: population category defined using ancestry informative markers (AIMs) based on genetic/genomic data

Subject: uncategorised population [HANCESTRO:0018]
Value: a population for which specific ancestry information is known but that does not fall into any of the defined ancestry categories

Subject: genetically isolated population [HANCESTRO:0290]
Value: a population with increased genetic homogeneity and reduced genetic variation due to cultural or geographic isolation

Subject: ancestry status [HANCESTRO:0304]
Value: general characterisation of the ancestry of a population or individual

Subject: undefined ancestry population [HANCESTRO:0566]
Value: population for which insufficient information is available to allocate it to a specific ancestral group or which contain individuals from a range of known ancestry categories, eg American
